  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Airport
    This class represents our datatype for the Airports in our system.
    Database
    The Database class allows for a simple interface between the program and the database.
    DatabaseAddMenu
    The DatabaseAddMenu class is the class that manages our Database menu in the system.
    FindMenu
    Enables the user to search the database for reservations, persons and flights.
    Flight
    This class represents our datatype for the Flights in our system.
    FlightInfoMenu
    This class is where the Flight Info Menu window is from.
    FlightManagerMenu
    A menu that the user can use in order to edit the passenger amount, the selected flight aswell as the passengers seats of a selected flight.
    FlightPanel
    The FlightPanel serves as a usable JPanel that can be implemented anywhere without further ado.
    JPanelWithBackground
    The JPanelWithBackground class is a class that creates a jpanel with a background image.
    JTextFieldUpgraded
    JTextFieldUpgraded is a class that we use in our PersonInfoEditorMenu.
    Main
    The sole purpose of this class is to isolate the main method in a single class
    MainMenu
    MainMenu creates the first window of the application.
    Passenger
    This class represents our datatype for the Passengers in our system.
    PassengerManagerMenu
    This class is the class that controls the window where the user inputs the details of all the persons of the current reservation.
    Person
    This class represents our datatype for the Persons in our system.
    PersonInfoEditorMenu
    This editor enables the user to edit a persons details.
    PersonInfoMenu
    PassengerInformationMenu presents an overview of a persons details and reservations.
    Plane
    This class represents our Plane datatype for the system.
    Reservation
    This class represents our datatype for the Reservations in our system.
    ReservationInfoMenu
    A menu that the user can use in order to access the information of a given reservation
    Seat
    This class represents our datatype for the Seats in our system.
    SeatButton
    A button, which represents a Seat in a FlightPanel.
